  <refnamediv>
    <refname>shotpanel</refname>
    <refpurpose>Control panel for executing audio routing salvos</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <info>
    <author>
      <personname>
	<firstname>Fred</firstname>
	<surname>Gleason</surname>
	<email>fredg@paravelsystems.com</email>
      </personname>
      <contrib>Application Author</contrib>
    </author>
  </info>

  <!--
      Body
  -->
  <refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>shotpanel</command>    <arg choice='opt'><replaceable>OPTIONS</replaceable></arg>
      <sbr/>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1 id='description'><title>Description</title>
  <para>
    <command>shotpanel</command><manvolnum>1</manvolnum> is an control
    applet that can be used to execute audio routing salvos with systems
    using the Software Authority control protocol (such as PathFinder or
    Drouter's
    <command>drouterd</command><manvolnum>8</manvolnum>).
  </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1 id='options'><title>Options</title>
  <variablelist remap='TP'>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--help</option>
      </term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Print a short usage message and then exit.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>

  <variablelist remap='TP'>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--hostname <replaceable>host-name</replaceable></option>
      </term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Use the Drouter server at <replaceable>host-name</replaceable>.
	  Default value is <userinput>localhost</userinput>. See also the
	  section ENVIRONMENTAL VARIABLES, below.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>

  <variablelist remap='TP'>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--initial-router=<replaceable>router-num</replaceable></option>
      </term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Select router number <replaceable>router-num</replaceable> after
	  startup. Default is to select the first router listed by the
	  <userinput>RouterNames</userinput> command.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>
      <option>--no-creds</option>
    </term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
	This option does nothing, and exists solely for backwards
	compatibility.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>
      <option>--password=<arg choice="req"><replaceable>pwd</replaceable></arg></option>
    </term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
	Password to use when authenticating on the server.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>
      <option>--prompt</option>
    </term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
	Prompt for Username and Password at startup.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>
      <option>--username=<arg choice="req"><replaceable>user-name</replaceable></arg></option>
    </term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
	The username to use when authenticating on the server. Default
	value is <userinput>shotpanel</userinput>.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <variablelist remap='TP'>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--version</option>
      </term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Print the version string and then exit.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>

  </refsect1>

  <refsect1 id='environmental_variables'>
    <title>Environmental Variables</title>
    <para>
      The following environmental variables can be used to influence
      the behavior of <command>shotpanel</command><manvolnum>1</manvolnum>: 
    </para>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
	<term><userinput>$DROUTER_HOSTNAME</userinput></term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    If no <option>--hostname</option> option is given,
	    <command>shotpanel</command><manvolnum>1</manvolnum> will
	    attempt to use the Drouter server referenced in
	    <userinput>$DROUTER_HOSTNAME</userinput>. If
	    <userinput>$DROUTER_HOSTNAME</userinput> is not defined,
	    then the Drouter server at <userinput>localhost</userinput>
	    will be used.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

